<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1629,2016]" pageId="29">
Extralimital distribution: Africa, Iberian Peninsula, southwestern Europe north to 
<collectingCountry box="[1071,1169,1918,1944]" name="Hungary" pageId="29">Hungary</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1224,1328,1917,1943]" name="Romania" pageId="29">Romania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Azerbaijan" pageId="29">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[287,367,1953,1979]" name="Turkey" pageId="29">Turkey</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[403,468,1953,1979]" name="Israel" pageId="29">Israel</collectingCountry>
, Transcaspia, 
<collectingCountry box="[625,720,1953,1979]" name="Pakistan" pageId="29">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[775,836,1953,1979]" name="India" pageId="29">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1629,2016]" lastBlockId="30.[199,1437,153,287]" lastPageId="30" pageId="29">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1918" box="[265,522,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Tachysphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvicornis">
<emphasis box="[265,522,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="29">Tachysphex fulvicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pulawski" authorityYear="1971" box="[575,729,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Tachysphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrifurci">
<emphasis box="[575,729,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="29">T. quadrifurci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were effectively synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mercet" authorityYear="1909" box="[1135,1292,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Tachysphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[1135,1292,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="29">T. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pulawski, W. J." lastPageId="30" pageId="29" pagination="1 - 698" refId="ref31801" refString="Pulawski, W. J. (2007). The wasp genus Tachysphex Kohl, 1883 of Sahara, sub-Saharan Africa, the Arabian Peninsula, and Madagascar (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Crabronidae). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 58 (Supplement 1), 1 - 698." type="journal article" year="2007">Pulawski (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Straka, J. &amp; Schmid-Egger, CH" box="[288,638,153,179]" pageId="30" pagination="417 - 461" refId="ref32615" refString="Straka, J. &amp; Schmid-Egger, CH. (2017) Order Hymenoptera, family Crabronidae. Genus Tachysphex Kohl, 1883. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 6, 417 - 461." type="journal article" year="2017">Straka &amp; Schmid-Egger (2017)</bibRefCitation>
treated both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1918" box="[784,932,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Tachysphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvicornis">
<emphasis box="[784,932,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="30">T. fulvicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pulawski" authorityYear="1971" box="[986,1140,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Tachysphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrifurci">
<emphasis box="[986,1140,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="30">T. quadrifurci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid species, however, stating that two morphological forms are present in the Arabian Peninsula. The synonymy of both with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mercet" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Tachysphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30">T. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reconfirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pulawski, W. J." box="[505,688,225,251]" pageId="30" refId="ref31944" refString="Pulawski, W. J. (2019) Catalogue of Sphecidae sensu lato (= Apoidea excluding Apidae). Available from: https: // www. calacademy. org / scientists / projects / catalog-of-sphecidae (accessed 8 December 2019)" type="url" year="2019">Pulawski (2019)</bibRefCitation>
who considered the evidence provided insufficient to justify Straka &amp; Schmid-Eggerâ€™s stance.
</paragraph>
